    "body": "### Problem\n\nSimilar to a previous issue I created: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32744, but only seems to manifest when the lines are at the top of the window. If you create 2 extmark:\n\n- at row 0 with `conceal_lines = ''`\n- at row 1 with some `virt_lines` & `virt_lines_above = true`\n\nAs you scroll passed the concealed line it'll cause the lines displayed to be offset / duplicated.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.conceallevel = 3\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWinEnter', {\n    callback = function()\n        local ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\n\n        -- This conceals 'Line 1'\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, {\n            conceal_lines = '',\n        })\n\n        -- This adds a virtual line above 'Line 2'\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, {\n            virt_lines = {\n                { { 'Virtual Line', 'DiffChange' } },\n            },\n            virt_lines_above = true,\n        })\n    end,\n})\n```\n\n2. `test.txt`:\n\n```text\nLine 1\nLine 2\nLine 3\nLine 4\nLine 5\n```\n\n3. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua test.txt`\n\n4. Scroll down to the 3rd line by pressing `j` 2 times (IMPORTANT this does not happen if you run `2j`, it only happens if you go line by line, though if you continue to scroll down with `j` after running `2j` you'll see other offset behavior)\n\n5. Observe that the line below the current one now shows `Line 3` (duplicating the current line) instead of `Line 4` and the line below that shows `Line 4` instead of `Line 5`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFollowing the steps to reproduce the issue:\n\n| Expected Display | Actual Display |\n| ----------------- | -------------- |\n| <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e87c5455-f830-4da1-ae75-837541771045\" /> | <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a93df32d-ddd8-4f87-85dd-da2bd7dba9f2\" /> |\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-2070+gf4d9a2983a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno: related to extmarks\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezTerm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
